claim.claim-text:
A method for sharing by a client device (202) content items using an online content management system (220) managing a plurality of namespaces, the client device having access to content items in a local content library (210) associated with a first namespace of the plurality of namespaces managed by the online content management system, the local content library synchronized with a remote content library (226) for the first namespace at the online content management system, the client device having access to content items stored externally to the local content library on the client device, the management of the content items of the remote content library associated with the first namespace comprising storing and synchronizing the content items associated with the first namespace at the online content management system with the content items associated with the first namespace in the local content library by the online content management system, the method comprising:
receiving, by the client device, a user input to generate a link for a content item stored externally to the local content library;
in response to the user input, generating, by the client device, a copy of the content item;
storing, by the client device, the copy of the content item in a cache (208) on the client device;
transmitting, by the client device, information describing the content item to the online content management system to store metadata for the content item in a second namespace of the plurality of namespaces at the online content management system distinct from the first namespace associated with the remote content library; and
receiving, from the online content management system, a link for accessing the copy of the content item stored at the online content management system associated with the second namespace distinct from the first namespace associated with the remote content library.

The method of claim 1, further comprising:
generating one or more first hash values based on content of the content item;
transmitting the one or more first hash values to the online content management system;
receiving one or more second hash values from the online content management system that correspond to a portion of the one or more first hash values; and
transmitting, to the online content management system, content of the content item corresponding to the one or more second hash values.

A method comprising:
receiving from a client device (202), at a server device of an online content management system (220) managing a plurality of namespaces, information describing a content item external to a local content library (210) associated with a first namespace of the plurality of namespaces, and external to a remote content library (226) associated with the first namespace, the remote content library being managed by the online content management system, the management of content items of the remote content library associated with the first namespace comprising storing and synchronizing the content items associated with the first namespace at the online content management system with the local content library associated with the first namespace by the online content management system;
generating a metadata entry in an external content database (228) of the online content management system using a second namespace of the plurality of namespaces for storing metadata for the content item separately from metadata representing the remote content library associated with the first namespace;
generating a link for accessing the metadata entry associated with the second namespace; and
transmitting the link to the client device of the online content management system.

A system comprising:
means for receiving from a client device (202), at a server device of an online content management system (220) managing a plurality of namespaces, information describing a content item external to a local content library (210) associated with a first namespace of the plurality of namespaces, and external to a remote content library (226) associated with the first namespace, the remote content library being managed by the online content management system, the management of managed content items of the remote content library associated with the first namespace comprising storing and synchronizing the managed content items at the online content management system with the local content library associated with the first namespace by the online content management system;
means for generating a metadata entry in an external content database (228) of the online content management system using a second namespace of the plurality of namespaces for storing metadata for the content item separately from metadata representing the remote content library associated with the first namespace;
means for generating a link for accessing the metadata entry associated with the second namespace; and
means for transmitting the link to a client device of the online content management system.

The system of claim 11, further comprising:
means for receiving one or more first hash values corresponding to content data of the content item;
means for comparing the first hash values to hash value indexes of a content data store of the online content management system;
means for determining which of the one or more hash values do not exist in the content data store based on the comparison; and
means for transmitting to the client device one or more second hash values corresponding to the one or more first hash values that do not exist in the content data store.
